-- Fema Says NY Sandy Survivors Got $564 Million in U.S. Aid
-- B y   W i l l   D a l e y
-- 2012-11-20T15:32:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-20/fema-says-ny-sandy-survivors-got-564-million-in-u-s-aid.html
The Federal Emergency Management
Agency said New York survivors of  Hurricane Sandy  have received
$564 million in federal individual assistance grants.  The assistance includes $531 million in housing grants and
$33 million to cover other essential disaster-related needs,
such as medical and dental expenses and lost personal
possessions, FEMA said today in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Daley at 
 wdaley2@bloomberg.net  